17 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Professional stipends for highly qualified teachers serving English
18 learners. (1) Pursuant to subsection (5), an annual stipend of up to $500 AN AMOUNT EQUIVALENT TO 50% OF THE
19 QUALITY EDUCATOR PAYMENT AMOUNT PROVIDED IN 20-9-306 FOR THE APPLICABLE YEAR must be provided to each
20 teacher who holds a culturally and linguistically diverse certificate or a teaching certificate with an English as a
21 second language endorsement if the teacher is:
22 (a) a classroom teacher serving students with limited English proficiency as defined in 20-1-101;
23 (b) certified to teach in the state under the provisions of 20-4-103; and
24 (c) a full-time employee of:
25 (i) a Montana public school district as defined in 20-6-101;
26 (ii) an education cooperative as described in 20-7-451;
27 (iii) the Montana school for the deaf and blind as described in 20-8-101; or
28 (iv) a correctional facility as defined in 41-5-103.
